title: .isDisjointFrom()
description: The `.isDisjointFrom()` JS method checks whether the current `Set` object has no elements in common with the `Set` object provided as an argument.
content: The method that checks whether the `Set` object on which it's called has no elements in common with the `Set` object passed as an argument. It returns `true` if they are disjoint, meaning they have no common elements and `false` if at least one element is shared.
